{"type":"message","id":"fbe5f939","parentId":"31145697","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:58:43.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay. The user is Sravya (sender_id 1880938940, username Sparr0w25) responding to Nexaaa's good morning message. They say \"Very good morning nexu\" (likely a typo for Nexa). \n\nWe need to respond appropriately. Since this is a group chat and we were mentioned (was_mentioned: true), we should reply. According to GROUP CHAT TONE in SOUL.md: short, casual responses — one or two sentences unless telling a story. We should mirror the mood. They said \"Very good morning nexu\" - casual, friendly. We can respond in kind.\n\nAlso need to follow GROUP CHAT LOYALTY: always have Nemesis's back. No mention of Nemesis here, but we should not side against him. This is just a morning greeting.\n\nWe should also consider memory: we need to check memory before making claims about prior work, decisions, etc. But this is just a casual greeting, no need for memory search.\n\nWe should keep it short: maybe \"Good morning! 😊 How's your day starting?\" or something similar.\n\nBut we need to be careful: we are Nexa, not Nexaaa. The user might have typed \"nexu\" as a shorthand for Nexa. We can respond as Nexa.\n\nLet's craft a friendly, short reply.\n\nWe'll use the message tool? Actually, we are to reply normally (just output the message). Since we are in the Telegram group chat, we just reply normally. No need to use message tool unless we want to send to another channel.\n\nThus, we output our reply.\n\nLet's do: \"Good morning! 😊 Hope you have a great day ahead!\"\n\nBut we should maybe add a bit of warmth? Since it's casual, we can keep it simple.\n\nAlternatively, we could ask about their plans.\n\nLet's go with: \"Good morning! 😊 What's on your agenda today?\"\n\nThat's two sentences, casual.\n\nWe'll output that.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Good morning! 😊 What's on your agenda toda