{"type":"message","id":"ed95d8af","parentId":"08ac7ee3","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:32:20.105Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1426\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1423\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-07 04:32 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\",\n  \"username\": \"Sparr0w25\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Have a productive day at the office! Let me know if you need anything while you're working. 💼\"\n}\n```\n\nHow to edit lightning record page label and api name in salesforce?"}],"timestamp":1775536340089}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a2df2cc","parentId":"ed95d8af","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:32:44.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, I need to help Sravya with editing a Lightning record page label and API name in Salesforce. I should provide clear, step-by-step instructions.\n\nFirst, I should confirm what exactly she wants to edit - the Lightning record page itself (which is a Lightning component), or perhaps an object's record page? In Salesforce, Lightning record pages are assigned to objects, and you can edit their properties.\n\nLet me think about the process:\n1. For editing a Lightning record page's label and API name, you typically need to go through the Lightning App Builder or Setup.\n2. The label is the display name, and the API name is the unique identifier used in code/APIs.\n\nSteps to edit:\n- Go to Setup (gear icon)\n- In the Quick Find box, type \"Lightning App Builder\"\n- Select Lightning App Builder\n- Find the record page you want to edit\n- Click the dropdown next to the page name and select \"Properties\" or similar\n- You should be able to edit the Label and API Name there\n\nAlternatively, if it's a custom object's record page:\n- Go to Setup\n- Object Manager\n- Select the object\n- Page Layouts or Lightning Record Pages\n- Find the specific record page\n- Edit its properties\n\nI should provide both approaches since I'm not sure exactly what she's referring to. Let me give clear instructions.\n\nAlso, I should note that changing the API name might have implications if there are references to it in code, flows, or other metadata.\n\nLet me craft a helpful response.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"To edit a Lightning record page's label and API name in Salesforce, follow these steps:\n\n## Method 1: Via Lightning App Builder\n1. Click the **Setup** (gear icon) in the top-right\n2. In the **Quick Find** box, type **\"Lightning App Builder\"** and select it\n3. Find the Lightning record page you want to edit in the list\n4. Click the **dropdown arrow** (▼) next to the page name\n5. Select **\"Properties\"**\n6. In the Properties panel:\n   - **Label**: Edit the display name (what users see)\n   - **API Name**: Edit the unique identifier (used in code/APIs)\n7. Click **Save**\n\n## Method 2: Via Object Manager (for object-specific record pages)\n1. Go to **Setup**\n2. Type **\"Object Manager\"** in Quick Find and select it\n3. Choose the **object** associated with the record page\n4. In the left sidebar, select **\"Lightning Record Pages\"**\n5. Find your record page, click the **dropdown arrow** (▼) next to it\n6. Select **\"Properties\"**\n7. Edit the **Label** and **API Name** as needed\n8. Click **Save**\n\n## Important Notes:\n- **API Name Changes**: Changing the API name may break references in Apex, Lightning components, flows, or metadata. Use **Setup → Migration Tools → Change Sets** or **Workbench** to check dependencies first.\n- **Label Changes**: Safe to modify anytime—only affects the user interface.\n- **Activation**: After saving, you may need to **activate** the page for it to take effect for users.\n- **Permissions**: Ensure you have the **\"Customize Application\"** permission.\n\nIf you're working with a managed package or have specific restrictions, let me know and I can provide more tailored guidance! 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":20390,"output":1105,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21495,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775536340105,"responseId":"gen-1775536340-sZh6i1nvL5Kmgt8pCMtD"}}
