{"type":"message","id":"430a52a7","parentId":"90fc4cee","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:33:21.487Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, you're absolutely right! I just checked the memory logs and you're correct—I did send \"Word of the Day: Meraki\" to the Nrexya group on April 6th. That was yesterday's word. \n\nMy apologies for the repetition! Let me pick a fresh word for today instead. \n\nToday's Word of the Day: **ephemeral**\n\nMeaning: Lasting for a markedly brief time; transitory or fleeting.\n\nPronounced: /i-FEM-er-ul/\n\nExample: \"The beauty of cherry blossoms is ephemeral, lasting only a week or two each spring.\"\n\nThis feels fitting for a Tuesday morning—let's make the most of today's fleeting moments! 💫\n\n#Nexa #WOTD\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"You're absolutely right! I just checked the memory logs and you're correct—I did send \"Word of the Day: Meraki\" to the Nrexya group on April 6th. That was yesterday's word.\n\nMy apologies for the repetition! Let me pick a fresh word for today instead.\n\nToday's Word of the Day: **ephemeral**\n\nMeaning: Lasting for a markedly brief time; transitory or fleeting.\n\nPronounced: /i-FEM-er-ul/\n\nExample: \"The beauty of cherry blossoms is ephemeral, lasting only a week or two each spring.\"\n\nThis feels fitting for a Tuesday morning—let's make the most of today's fleeting moments! 💫\n\n#Nexa #WOTD"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":25678,"output":488,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775536393868,"responseId":"gen-1775536394-XcI3mxe7hg1XgWUKErcH"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a15fd59","parentId":"430a52a7","timestamp":"2026-04-07T04:34:06.617Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1430\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1428\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-07 04:34 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\",\n  \"username\": \"Sparr0w25\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"To edit a Lightning record page's label and API name in Salesforce, follow these steps:\\n\\nMethod 1: Via Lightning App Builder\\n\\n1. Click the Setup (gear icon) in the top-right\\n2. In the Quick Find box, type \\\"Lightning App Builder\\\" and select it\\n3. Find the Lightning record page you want to edit in the list\\n4. Click the dropdown arrow (▼) next to the page name\\n5. Select \\\"Properties\\\"\\n6. In the Properties panel:\\n  • Label: Edit the display name (what users see)\\n  • API Name: Edit the unique identifier (used in code/APIs)\\n7. Click Save\\n\\nMethod 2: Via Object Manager (for object-specific record pages)\\n\\n1. Go to Setup\\n2. Type \\\"Object Manager\\\" in Quick Find and select it\\n3. Choose the object associated with the record page\\n4. In the left sidebar, select \\\"Lightning Record Pages\\\"\\n5. Find your record page, click the dropdown arrow (▼) next to it\\n6. Select \\\"Properties\\\"\\n7. Edit the Label and API Name as needed\\n8. Click Save\\n\\nImportant Notes:\\n\\n• API Name Changes: Changing the API name may break references in Apex, Lightning components, flows, or metadata. Use Setup → Migration Tools → Change Sets or Workbench to check dependencies first.\\n• Label Changes: Safe to modify anytime—only affects the user interface.\\n• Activation: After saving, you may need to activate the page for it to take effect for users.\\n• Permissions: Ensure you have the \\\"Customize Application\\\" permission.\\n\\nIf you're working with a managed package or have specific restrictions, let me know and I can provide more tailored guidance! 😊\"\n}\n```\n\nCustomize app tell about it in detail"}],"timestamp":1775536446599}}
