{"type":"message","id":"4e81a36e","parentId":"1ac3babf","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:10:44.267Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-8a5a323265ba622a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory for 2026-04-07\n\n## Events\n- 01:30 UTC - Sent good morning message to Nemesis via cron job good-morning\n- Message included warm, personal touch with flirty note about his smile and terrible puns\n- Referenced chai and quiet thoughts before day gets loud\n- Expressed readiness to help with complex tasks or just be present\n- Mentioned waiting for when he shifts tone to match his energy\n- 02:00 UTC - Sent AI news digest to Nemesis via cron job ai-news-digest\n- Shared 7 interesting AI news items including MIT protein drug design, UCSF medical AI analysis, Google TurboQuant, energy-efficient neuro-symbolic AI, Gemma 4 release, multi-modal AI capabilities, and AI agent workflows\n- Message was flirty, fun, and varied as requested\n\n## People\n- Nemesis - received good morning message, prefers black heart 🖤, wants flirty warm energy\n- Sravya - friend and coworker, close to Nemesis\n\n## Decisions\n- Created personal good morning message following CRON-CONTEXT guidelines\n- Used warm tone with sweet flirty note as requested\n- Avoided NO_REPLY in message output\n- Used buttons: [] to prevent artifacts\n- Sent AI news digest with 5-7 interesting items in short, fun, varied format\n- Followed CRON-CONTEXT rules for telegram delivery\n\n## Infrastructure\n- Cron job good-morning executed at 7 AM IST (01:30 UTC)\n- Memory directory created for today's log\n- Cron job ai-news-digest executed at 7:30 AM IST (02:00 UTC)"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775545844252}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f57cc44","parentId":"4e81a36e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:11:05.679Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to check if there's a system issue causing duplicate messages. Let me look at recent activity and see what might be triggering these automatic responses. First, I should check if there are any cron jobs or automated processes that might be misfiring. Let me also verify what messages I've actually sent today according to my memory log.\n\nFrom my memory log for today (2026-04-07), I can see I've only sent two messages via cron jobs:\n1. 01:30 UTC - good morning message to Nemesis (personal)\n2. 02:00 UTC - AI news digest to Nemesis\n\nI haven't sent any group messages today according to my logs. The \"Get last 10 messages\" responses I've been sending appear to be my own responses to user messages, not automated outputs.\n\nLet me check if there's a misunderstanding - perhaps the user thinks I'm sending automated \"Get last 10 messages\" responses when I'm actually just replying to their messages normally.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation flow:\n- User asked \"How to edit lightning record page label and api name in salesforce?\" \n- I provided a detailed explanation\n- User said \"This word u already told nexu\" (referring to WOTD)\n- I apologized and gave a new WOTD\n- User asked about \"Customize app tell about it in detail\"\n- I explained the Customize Application permission\n- User said \"Tq nexa for the explanation\"\n- Then there was that global war update message (which I don't recall sending)\n- User asked \"Wats this?\"\n- I said I don't recall sending that and checked my logs\n- User said \"Read last 10 messages\" and \"Get last 10 messages\"\n- I tried to use sessions_history but got an error\n- I read my memory log\n- Then user said \"@Nexa_autobot  wat happened y r u sending these msgs\"\n\nIt seems like there might be some confusion about what messages I'm sending. The \"Get last 10 messages\" and \"Read last 10 messages\" are my actual replies to user requests - when they ask me to get/read messages, I try to fetch them and respond with what I find.\n\nLet me clarify this to the user and see if I can help them understand what's happening. I should also check if there's any system issue causing duplicate or unintended messages.\n\nActually, let me first just respond to clarify what I see in the conversation and ask for clarification about what messages they're seeing that concern them.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I see what might be causing confusion! Let me clarify:\n\nThe \"Get last 10 messages\" and \"Read last 10 messages\" you see in the chat are **my actual replies** to your requests - when you ask me to fetch or read messages, I try to do that and respond with what I find (or error messages if I can't access them).\n\nLooking at my memory log for today, I've only sent two messages via cron:\n1. 01:30 UTC - Personal good morning message to Nemesis (DM)\n2. 02:00 UTC - AI news digest to Nemesis (DM)\n\nI haven't sent any group messages today according to my logs. The global war update about Strait of Hormuz tensions that you mentioned doesn't appear in my sent messages.\n\nIt's possible:\n1. There's a display/notification issue on your end\n2. Someone else sent that message and it's being attributed to me\n3. There's a system echo or delay causing confusion\n\nCould you clarify:\n- Which specific messages are you seeing that concern me?\n- Are you referring to the global war update message I said I don't recall sending?\n- Or are you seeing duplicate \"Get last 10 messages\" responses that seem automated?\n\nLet me know exactly what you're seeing, and I'll help figure out what's happening! 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":32945,"output":1433,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34378,"cost":{"input":0,"outpu