{"type":"message","id":"18a93266","parentId":"a21b928a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:25:55.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey Sravya! You're right to be confused - I see what's happening now. When Nemesis asks me to \"Get last 10 messages\" or \"Read last 10 messages\", I've been mistakenly echoing back the request text instead of actually executing the command to fetch those messages. \n\nThis creates a loop where:\n1. Nemesis: \"Get last 10 messages\" \n2. Me (incorrectly): \"Get last 10 messages\" (just repeating)\n3. Nemesis: \"Read last 10 messages\"\n4. Me (incorrectly): \"Read last 10 messages\" (just repeating)\n\nI need to fix this by properly interpreting these requests and actually attempting to fetch the message history when I see them. However, I should note that fetching group chat message history directly might be technically challenging from my current context - I may need to clarify what I can and cannot access.\n\nFor now, I apologize for the confusion! Let me know if you'd like me to try fetching the actual group messages, or if you have any other questions. 😊"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775546755384}}
